    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-14T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-14T02:00:00-05:00" n="452"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d452">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9370: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-14T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 14, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>429. Chinese authorities state that three squadrons of planes this morning bombed
                    and set on fire Japanese landing force headquarters and the Kunzta factory where
                    Japanese ammunition is stored and <pb facs="0415" n="408" xml:id="pg_408"/>
                    attempted to bomb Japanese cruiser <hi rend="italic">Idzumo</hi> but missed and
                    hit wharf. Also several Chinese planes were hit, only one has as yet failed to
                    return.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department, Peiping, Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
